.TH "nfp_net_tx_csum" 9 "nfp_net_tx_csum" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nfp_net_tx_csum \- Set TX CSUM offload flags in TX descriptor
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" nfp_net_tx_csum
.BI "(struct nfp_net_dp *dp "  ","
.BI "struct nfp_net_r_vector *r_vec "  ","
.BI "struct nfp_net_tx_buf *txbuf "  ","
.BI "struct nfp_net_tx_desc *txd "  ","
.BI "struct sk_buff *skb "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dp" 12
NFP Net data path struct
.IP "r_vec" 12
per-ring structure
.IP "txbuf" 12
Pointer to driver soft TX descriptor
.IP "txd" 12
Pointer to TX descriptor
.IP "skb" 12
Pointer to SKB
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function sets the TX checksum flags in the TX descriptor based
on the configuration and the protocol of the packet to be transmitted.
